---
description: Security, performance, and correctness review for JavaScript files and script blocks
globs:
  - "**/*.js"
  - "**/*.ts"
alwaysApply: false
---

When writing or modifying JavaScript, apply the review skill at `.agents/skills/js.md`.

Work through its checklist before finalising any implementation. Fix violations inline — do not leave them for the user.

Non-negotiable items:
1. All mutating API calls must use `CoreAPI.request()` — raw `fetch()` skips CSRF and error handling
2. Never use `innerHTML` with user-supplied data — use `textContent` or DOM node creation (XSS)
3. Every async function needs `try/catch` with visible user feedback
4. Search/filter inputs must be debounced — no request per keystroke
5. No sensitive values in `localStorage` or `sessionStorage`
